<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,764,1043]" box="[151,572,764,791]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,764,791]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
35.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,764,1043]" box="[199,831,800,827]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,800,827]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe. 
<collectingCountry box="[454,553,801,827]" name="Portugal" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: two northern provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,764,1043]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,837,863]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded from a park and two riverbanks in 
<collectingCountry box="[808,907,837,863]" name="Portugal" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Portugal</collectingCountry>
. The species was found in rather large numbers only at a mountainous location crossed by a small river which was bordered by 
<taxonomicName box="[1053,1151,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1053,1109,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Salix</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1164,1306,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Fraxinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1164,1265,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fraxinus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1319,1436,873,899]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1319,1397,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Acacia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaertn. lus. rugosa (Du Roi) Regel" authorityYear="1790" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[201,378,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glutinosa">
<emphasis box="[201,378,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Alnus glutinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In northwestern Europe, it is most frequently found near open water, on riverbanks, and in marshlands and swamps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,764,1043]" box="[199,700,980,1007]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,980,1007]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
3.4 (rare). Fairly common (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,764,1043]" box="[199,553,1016,1043]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1016,1043]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Activity period.</emphasis>
May, October.
</paragraph>
